Code, Cap.37, Vol.1, Laws of Ondo State 2006. The defendant, however, pleaded not guilty. Chief Magistrate Mosunmola Ikujuni admitted the defendant to bail in the sum of N500,000 with one surety in like sum. Ikujuni ordered that the surety must present evidence of one year tax clearance. She adjourned the case until Sept. 30 for further hearing. [NAN] Vanguard News Nigeria. The police on Tuesday arraigned a trader, Folashade Iwalokun, in an Okitipupa Chief Magistrates’ Court, Ondo for allegedly biting and punching one Ope Omotehinde in the back. April 16, 2019 In "News" Two men, Olatunjoye Adelure, 52 and Inumidun Adeye, 59, on Friday appeared before an Okitipupa Chief Magistrate’s Court in Ondo State for allegedly damaging the foundation laid for a house. The defendants — a tailor and a bricklayer — of unknown addresses, were standing trial in the court on a… December 13, 2019 In "Metro" Two brothers, Sunday Ikuedowo, 35, and Olumide Ikuedowo, 25, were on Friday arraigned in an Okitipupa Magistrates’ Court in Ondo State over alleged theft of Christmas chickens valued at N25,000. January 26, 2018 In "News"